summary:
Look at which direction TJ ran from-  
He clearly ran from a short distance since it didn’t take him much time at all to catch...
body:
I was watching 3x06 and I noticed something….

Look at which direction TJ ran from-

He clearly ran from a short distance since it didn’t take him much time at all to catch up with Cyrus. He came from the right hand side but further right like a wall or corner. As they’re walking, a wall is shown.

You guys.

TJ waited for Cyrus to ask him to hang out.

He waited.

Now when they hang out.

Cyrus is wearing Reed’s gloves, vest and helmet, but he’s on TJ’s bike.

TJ said “Push in the uhh shifter, right?” When teaching Cyrus the mechanics of the bike. He said “Right?” As if Cyrus knew. He completely lost his train of thought just by the touch of Cyrus’s hand.

Smitten.

summary: Andi Mack x One Day at a Time comparison
body:
Andi Mack x One Day at a Time comparison

A list of the positive things about each show and their similarities.

  • a mainly poc cast (one day at a time centers around a cuban-american family) (out of the main characters in AM 2/4 are poc.)
  • lgbtq+ characters (ODAAT has lgbtq characters including but not limited to a lesbian/s and a non-binary character.) ( Andi Mack has (as far as we know) a gay character)
  • They frequently mention mental health and positive ways to deal with it. (ODAAT has a main character with anxiety and PTSD + other characters with similar mental health issues. The character openly goes to therapy and takes proper medication for her anxiety.) (Andi Mack has a main character that suffers from panic attacks)
  • Both of the shows have characters that have been or are in some form of the US army. Both characters are parents and in ODAAT they speak about their times in the army frequently)
  • They both center around single parent families (for now, there is a possibility that Andi Mack will change)

summary: And I just have to say, exploiting someone’s sexuality for your own personal gain is homophobic. It doesn’t necessarily mean...
body:
So I found this…

And I just have to say, exploiting someone’s sexuality for your own personal gain is homophobic. It doesn’t necessarily mean Kira herself is grossed out by it, but homophobia comes in many different forms. Manipulating someone by making them feel bad for being gay is homophobic whether she meant it that way or not.

blog.description: Lola| 22 years old| Tyrus Shipper| Trans Woman| Disney Fan| Charmed Fan| Harry Potter Fan

body:
Falling In Love~Tyrus Chapter 23

Lola’s POV

I’m still in shock that I have now lost both my parents in a fire. How did this even happen? I’m grateful for Jonah and his mom for taking me in. I don’t know what I would do without them.

Jonah’s POV

I’m trying to be a good boyfriend for Lola and be there in her time of need. I have no idea what she must be feeling right now.

Andi’s POV

Jonah and Lola are a cute couple and I’m glad Lola has him with her in this difficult time. Losing both parents just like that… I can’t believe what she’s going through.

Tj’s POV

My aunt and uncle.. gone in a flash.. how could this have happened?

Amber’s POV

Mom has been silent this past week. I can’t believe this.. why would God do this to our family?

Eva’s POV

God must be punishing us for having so many fags in our family.

Marty’s POV

So I recently discovered that I’m bi and now my aunt and uncle are dead? Is this a punishment? I would like to call mom but her and my sisters went on a mother daughter trip.. does Lola know that he… She… was our older sister?
